<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM2.3.13">
<l>vārkātu tāḻap perukki yamaittu</l>
<l rend="indent">makarak kuḻaiyiṭa vēṇṭic</l>
<l>cīrā lacōtai tirumālaic coṉṉacoṟ</l>
<l rend="indent">cintaiyuḷ niṉṟu tikaḻap</l>
<l>pārār tolpuka ḻāṉputu vaimaṉṉaṉ</l>
<l rend="indent">paṉṉiru nāmattāṟ coṉṉa</l>
<l>vārāta vantāti paṉṉiraṇ ṭumvallā</l>
<l rend="indent">raccuta ṉukkaṭi yārē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master all twelve antāti [verses],</l>
<l rend="indent">that were spoken along with the twelve names</l>
<l>without being satisfied,</l>
<l>by the king of Putuvai, he with with ancient fame</l>
<l rend="indent">that fills the earth,</l>
<l>so that the words that were said about holy Māl</l>
<l rend="indent">by Yaśodā with excellence,</l>
<l>having desired to place the Makara earrings</l>
<l>making [his] long ears expand so that they hang low,</l>
<l>shine, remaining in the mind,</l>
<l rend="indent">they are the slaves of Acyuta.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
